        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer373244656" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9975868717323255106">I remember thinking that this book was the most boring of the series when I was younger. Now, I don&apos;t think it was the most boring but definitely not my favorite. Just a little slower moving in parts and the whole Farrell and Kate love story seemed unreal. Even in my old age the difference between a 26-year-old and a 41-year-old seem immense. I have also realized that there often &quot;swarthy&quot; faces and answering &quot;tartly&quot;, and &quot;amused glances&quot; in the Mrs. Pollifax books.</span>
  <span id="freeText9975868717323255106" style="display:none">I remember thinking that this book was the most boring of the series when I was younger. Now, I don't think it was the most boring but definitely not my favorite. Just a little slower moving in parts and the whole Farrell and Kate love story seemed unreal. Even in my old age the difference between a 26-year-old and a 41-year-old seem immense. I have also realized that there often "swarthy" faces and answering "tartly", and "amused glances" in the Mrs. Pollifax books.</span>
