<span id="freeTextContainer376410345421191325">Assignment: Sicily. Farrell (first introduced in The Unexpected Mrs. Pollifax) who was the only male who ever referred to Emily as &quot;Duchess&quot; sent an SOS to his former employer from the island that most people would always associate with the Mafia. Farell had retired from the business that had given Emily a second life despite its perils... while the burnt out Farrell was happy and content to manage an art gallery in Mexico City and it was as an art connoisseur that saw him in Sicily and gave him</span>
  <span id="freeText376410345421191325" style="display:none">Assignment: Sicily. Farrell (first introduced in The Unexpected Mrs. Pollifax) who was the only male who ever referred to Emily as "Duchess" sent an SOS to his former employer from the island that most people would always associate with the Mafia. Farell had retired from the business that had given Emily a second life despite its perils... while the burnt out Farrell was happy and content to manage an art gallery in Mexico City and it was as an art connoisseur that saw him in Sicily and gave him a shock when he perceived an assassin that he helped send to jail apparently free and scouting for property in Sicily under an assumed name with a wife and as lunch guests of Farrell's client and present employer. Apparently limping with an infected bullet wound on his ankle (from a burglary for his client), starving and unwashed hiding in a root cellar from his relentless pursuers, he was a pathetic sight for their meeting and a far cry from his usual debonair playboy self. Emily and the rest of the people inadvertently involved in this caper thought he was hallucinating. He was not. An entertaining good read with endearing and interesting new characters. Layers of deep but pragmatic decisions and actions also some funny romantic moments for some characters.</span>
  <a data-text-id="376410345421191325" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
